description:
Oil paintings dates back to at least the seventh century CE, when unknown artisans decorated the ancient cave complex in Bamiyan, Afghanistan, using oil that may have been made from walnuts or poppies. However, the use of oil as a painting medium in Europe doesn't begin until the 11th century. However, tempera painting methods from the 15th century are directly responsible for easel painting with oil colors today.
